question.title: Why is openjdk:21 now missing from Docker Hub?
question.body:
Apparently the OpenJDK distribution for Java 21 is missing from Docker Hub. What happened? I'm certain OpenJDK 21 images existed in these paths before, as I've checked other successful deployments I have done in the past and all of the Dockerfiles had the openjdk:21 image path in it.

I have tried using the following images: openjdk:21, openjdk:21-jdk and openjdk:21-oracle

The Docker Hub website returns a 404.
